    <p>(c) The function changes from increasing to decreasing at <m>x=-3</m>, so there is a local maximum at <m>x=-3</m>.
          The function changes from decreasing to increasing at <m>x=3</m>, so there is a local minimum at <m>x=3</m>.
          At <m>x=0</m>, the derivative is zero but the function is decreasing on both sides, so <m>x=0</m> is neither a local maximum nor a local minimum.
 </p>

